apihelp-query+wikilambdasearch_functions: Search for Functions that have any label matching the substring <kbd>Engl</kbd> and are fully "renderable"
Search for Functions that have two input Strings and output another String
This API query list generator lets you search Functions by matching labels and input/output type filters. It principally exists to support Wikifunctions integration in Wikipedia.
Preferred language to return the result labels. If the preferred language is not available, the label in the closest fallback will be returned instead

Restrict matches to Functions that have only "renderable" inputs and outputs.
"Renderable" inputs can be Strings, Enums or types that have a reading function.
"Renderable" outputs can be Strings or any types that have a display function. If this parameter is set to true, the <var>input_type</var> and <var>output_type</var> parameters will be ignored.
Restrict matches to Functions that use at least the given input types. If <var>renderable</var> is <kbd>true</kbd>, this parameter is ignored.
Restrict matches to Functions that return the given type. If <var>renderable</var> is <kbd>true</kbd>, this parameter is ignored.
The maximum number of results to return
apihelp-query+wikilambdasearch_labels-su: This API query list generator lets you search ZObjects for labels in a given language. It principally exists to support the look-ahead search system.
apihelp-query+wikilambdasearch_labels-pa: The MediaWiki language code in which to search
Whether to search only in the given language and not its fallback languages
Whether to search for exact matches. If disabled, input will be taken as a case-insensitive, Unicode-normalised search with accents on Latin characters ignored.
Restrict matches to a specific type of ZObject.
Restrict matches to ZFunctions that can return the given type, including those who return a generic ZObject.
Restrict return type to be strictly the given one, excluding generic ZObject.
The maximum number of results to return
apihelp-query+wikilambda-example-simple: Search for ZObjects whose label matches 'foo' in English
apihelp-query+wikilambda-example-nofallb: Search for ZObjects whose label matches 'foo' in French, and don't accept fallback languages
apihelp-query+wikilambda-example-type: Search for ZObjects of type 'Z4', returning English labels
apihelp-query+wikilambda-example-return-: Search for ZObjects of return type 'Z40' or 'Z1', returning English labels
apihelp-query+wikilambda-example-strict-: Search for ZObjects of return type strictly 'Z40', returning English labels
apihelp-query+wikilambdaload_zobjects-su: Search ZObjects given their ZIDs and return their JSON model fully or filtered to a given language or fallbacks. If any of the provided ZIDs does not exist in the wiki, will return a Z5 error instead of the requested ZObject.
apihelp-query+wikilambdaload_zobjects-pa: The revision IDs to fetch. Must be empty or the same number as the number of ZIDs requested.
The MediaWiki language code in which to return all the ZObject labels.
Whether to return the canonical form or, if disabled, the partially normal form of the requested ZObjects. This partial normalization excludes ZLists, ZMonolingual Strings and ZMultilingual Strings.
Whether to return also the ZObjects that are dependencies of the originally requested ZIDs.
apihelp-query+wikilambdaload_zobjects-ex: Search for ZObjects Z12 and Z4 and return their full JSON representation.
Search for ZObjects Z12 and Z4 and return their labels filtered to Spanish or fallback languages.
Search for ZObjects Z1 and the non-existent Z012345789 and return their full JSON representation.
Search for ZObject Z12 and return its JSON canonical representation.
